The paper deals with semantic segmentation of 3D point clouds using deep learning techniques. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of multi-stream network architecture, which involves the integration of multiple modalities such as color, depth, and surface normals. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of projection techniques, which may be relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category, as semantic segmentation of 3D point clouds is an important task in robotics applications such as autonomous navigation.
